Static Nested Block vs Dynamic Block in Terraform

──────────────────────────────────────────────
Static Nested Block

resource "aws_security_group" "web" {
  ingress {
    from_port = 80
    to_port   = 80
    protocol  = "tcp"
  }
}

This is a static nested block:
• Manually written
• Fixed values
• Used when number of blocks is known

──────────────────────────────────────────────
Dynamic Block

resource "aws_security_group" "web" {
  dynamic "ingress" {
    for_each = [80, 443]

    content {
      from_port = ingress.value
      to_port   = ingress.value
      protocol  = "tcp"
    }
  }
}

This is a dynamic block:
• Uses dynamic + for_each
• Generates multiple nested blocks
• Used when values are from variables/list/map

──────────────────────────────────────────────
Terraform Generates

ingress {
  from_port = 80
  to_port   = 80
  protocol  = "tcp"
}

ingress {
  from_port = 443
  to_port   = 443
  protocol  = "tcp"
}

──────────────────────────────────────────────
Interview Answer

A static block is a manually defined nested block in Terraform.
A dynamic block uses the "dynamic" keyword with "for_each"
to generate multiple nested blocks automatically based on input
values, making the configuration flexible and reusable.
